					<h3 class="elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default">Market Share and Size</h3>				</div>
				</div>
				<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-2d83abdc elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id="2d83abdc" data-element_type="widget" data-e-type="widget" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
				<div class="elementor-widget-container">
									The <strong>Chartered Supply Chain Technology Manager (CSCT)®</strong> certification equips professionals with the expertise to navigate and lead in the rapidly expanding supply chain technology sector. In 2023, the global supply chain management market was valued at approximately USD 23.58 billion and is projected to grow to USD 63.77 billion by 2032, exhibiting a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 11.7% during the forecast period.								</div>
				</div>
				<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-6128c46 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id="6128c46" data-element_type="widget" data-e-type="widget" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
				<div class="elementor-widget-container">
									Fortune Business Insights								</div>
				</div>
				<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-b3a1a8a elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id="b3a1a8a" data-element_type="widget" data-e-type="widget" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
				<div class="elementor-widget-container">
									Artificial Intelligence (AI) is a significant contributor to this growth. The AI in supply chain market was estimated at USD 5.05 billion in 2023 and is expected to grow at a CAGR of 38.9% from 2024 to 2030. 								</div>
				</div>
					</div>
		</div>
